init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world has progressed well in advancement of industry, technology, and culture.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president emerged from the White House in his new copper armor and boots and told the American people that he was going to rebuild America as it once was

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The president vowed to use all of his weapons on any country and city that stood in the way of America becoming what it once was.
